Agree, but pushing back strongly against calls to regulate by companies that spend $millions and need ROI makes sense. People experimenting vs letting fear narratives drive regulation preserves our agency to define new uses and deployments. Essential to nurturing a collective literacy in how we use AI and what for.

Impressed with on/off ramp speed and ease with EURe on monerium. Did tests with stable coin -> EURe -> normal money in bank account - and back. It was mostly instant or next day in bank ac. Cost was zero. I think gnosis or monerium are covering gas?

also given USDC to EURe tx costs were around $20-30 on low gas when I did this, it drastically brings down costs of conversion vs using exchanges who work on % fees. Kind of feels like what Wise banking did for currency conversion, but for crypto on/off ramp.
There's going to be a bunch of onchain business workflows that emerge just on this.
